hu.invitech.insight.processor.sdk.v1.api

Interface FunctionInterface


  • public interface FunctionInterface
    Provides a service for getting information about available resource functions and calling functions on managed resources.

    This service needs to be accessible at the following path: /v1 "/function"

    Version:
    1

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FunctionReturn callFunction(FunctionCall functionCall)
      Calls a function on a resource with the supplied parameters.
      FunctionMap getFunctionMap()
      Returns the description of available functions for each resource type.

    • Method Detail

      • getFunctionMap

        FunctionMap getFunctionMap()
        Returns the description of available functions for each resource type.

        Needs JWT bearer authorization and should return HTTP 401 if the token is missing or invalid.

        Should be accessible at the following path: GET /

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is not assigned or it was previously assigned to a different server than the caller
        200 OK OK
        Returns:
        the description of available functions mapped by resource type (see FunctionMap)
        Since:
        version 1

      • callFunction

        FunctionReturn callFunction(FunctionCall functionCall)
        Calls a function on a resource with the supplied parameters.

        Needs JWT bearer authorization and should return HTTP 401 if the token is missing or invalid.

        Should be accessible at the following path: POST /

        HTTP status codes
        Code Text Description
        403 Forbidden The token is not assigned or it was previously assigned to a different server than the caller
        400 Bad Request A function with the name in FunctionCall.functionName doesn't exist
        404 Not Found A resource with the id in FunctionCall.resourceId doesn't exist
        500 Internal Server Error The function call encountered an unrecoverable error
        200 OK OK
        Parameters:
        functionCall - the function call description (see FunctionCall)
        Returns:
        the return values of the function (see FunctionReturn)
        Since:
        version 1
